What is VirtualBox?
VirtualBox is a free and open-source virtualization software developed by Oracle. It allows users to run multiple virtual machines (VMs) on a single physical machine. Each VM operates like an independent computer, running its own OS.

What is Kali Linux?
Kali Linux is a Debian-based Linux distribution designed for penetration testing, cybersecurity, and ethical hacking. It comes pre-installed with hundreds of security tools like Metasploit, Wireshark, Nmap, Burp Suite, etc.

Downloading & Installing VirtualBox
Step 1: Download VirtualBox
Go to the official VirtualBox website: https://www.virtualbox.org/
.Click on "Download VirtualBox".
.Select the correct version for your OS (Windows, macOS, or Linux).

Step 2: Install VirtualBox
.Run the downloaded .exe file
.Click "Install" and wait for completion.

Step 3: Verify Installation
.Open VirtualBox.
Downloading Kali Linux ISO
Step 1: Visit Kali Linux Official Website
.Go to: https://www.kali.org/get-kali/

Step 2: Choose the Right ISO
.Select "Kali Linux VirtualBox Image" (recommended for beginners).

Step 3: Download the ISO
.Click "Download" and wait for the .iso file to save.
